# Restoration Plan: Company Table

## Goal
Restore the `company` table data in the Staging environment (`future_sign_stage`) which was accidentally truncated. Since no local backup contains this data, we will replicate the data from the Production environment (`future_sign_prod`).

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Data Source**: Data will be copied from **Production** (`future_sign_prod`) to **Staging** (`future_sign_stage`).
>
> **Data Loss**: Any "Staging-only" companies created recently (that are not in Production) are permanently lost, as they are not in the discovered local backups. This operation only restores companies that exist in Production.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Scripts

#### [NEW] [restore_company_from_prod.py](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/scripts/restore_company_from_prod.py)
- Connect to MySQL Server.
- Read `future_sign_prod.company` data.
- Insert into `future_sign_stage.company`.
- **Preserve IDs**: Ensure `id` values are identical to maintain relationships with `member_company`.
- **Foreign Keys**: Temporarily disable FK checks during insertion.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
- Run the script: `python backend/scripts/restore_company_from_prod.py`
- Check row count in Staging: `SELECT COUNT(*) FROM future_sign_stage.company`
- Compare with Production: `SELECT COUNT(*) FROM future_sign_prod.company`

### Manual Verification
- User to check the Staging App or Database to confirm companies are visible again.
